WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Cultural contribution Hello class, today we're going to explore the amazing cultural

00:08.000 --> 00:14.960
contributions of the United Arab Emirates, a country full of creativity, tradition, and global ideas.

00:17.040 --> 00:23.120
Think of the UAE's culture like a glowing lantern-sharing light, warmth, and beauty with the world.

00:24.080 --> 00:30.000
From the past to today, people from this region have made contributions that still inspire others.

00:32.720 --> 00:39.040
Before the UAE was formed in 1971, the region was part of the Arabian Peninsula

00:39.040 --> 00:45.600
and was home to many great scholars. One of them was Imam Ahmad Ibn Hanbal,

00:46.160 --> 00:55.760
780 to 855 CE. He wrote Moussnat Ahmad Ibn Hanbal, a large book of Hadith. His teachings helped guide

00:55.760 --> 01:07.840
Muslim life. Ibn Haldun, 1332 to 1406 CE, was another famous thinker. He wrote the Makadema,

01:07.840 --> 01:14.240
a book that explains how history works. Many people call him the first real historian and sociologist.

01:16.320 --> 01:21.920
These scholars show that the Arabian Peninsula was a center of knowledge that helped shape the world.

01:23.840 --> 01:29.760
Today, the Sheikh Zaid grand mosque in Abu Dhabi shows how art and architecture continue

01:29.760 --> 01:35.280
to share the UAE's culture. It's peaceful white domes, welcome people from all around the world.

01:38.240 --> 01:43.840
Cultural influence continues today. The UAE is full of talented people making a difference.

01:44.800 --> 01:51.680
Aza al-Kubasi is the UAE's first jewelry designer. She uses palm fronds, desert stones,

01:51.680 --> 01:58.640
and pearls in her artwork. Her angel tears collection honors the UAE's pearl-diving history.

02:00.880 --> 02:06.800
Abdul Qadr al-Rais is a famous painter. His art uses Arabic calligraphy, colors,

02:06.800 --> 02:12.560
and shapes to show memory, identity, and culture. His work is shown around the world.

02:14.320 --> 02:21.040
Dr. Mariam Matar is a scientist and health leader. She started the Sheikh Zaid Genetic Research Center

02:21.040 --> 02:23.680
and teaches people about diseases like thalassemia.

02:25.760 --> 02:31.520
The UAE also celebrates its culture with big events like Expo 2020 Dubai,

02:31.520 --> 02:38.000
the Sheikh Zaid Heritage Festival, and National Day. People enjoy traditions like camel racing,

02:38.960 --> 02:44.480
alayala dance, Arabic music, and Emirati hospitality.

02:46.160 --> 02:52.240
Even today, Emirati art, language, and music connect the UAE with the world.

